divs: Sighting DetailsWas looking up at Ursa Major from my front porch, when I noticed movement, I thought it was a satellite very dim and high moving from the West to the East at about the speeds most satellites move across the sky. Suddenly it took a straight 90 degree turn to the south at double the speed it was initially traveling and shot out of sight. I have seen lots of satellites, but how this thing turned on a dime, and increased speed tells me it was no satellite and impossible for anything man made to pull this maneuver. It gave me chills.
